channel.title: Dinged proc, should I RMA?
channel.description:
My pc overheated or something, in the end i fried my onboard graphics n sound. So i RMA'd the mobo, but in the process of moving my cousin in, my HSF fell over and hit my proc where i had em sitting. the ding is fairly small, and if your not looking for it you can barely see it, my proc looks like this, http://images.wikio.com/images/s/64/amd-athlon-64-x2-3800.jpg, the ding is, in that picture full size, like an inch below the big x in x2. My proc has a 3 year manufacturers warrenty, should I RMA it now, or will it be good?
They fucked up at the ups place and mis sorted it so its not gunna get here for awhile, so i cant plug it in and see what happens.
